              <div style="display:grid;gap:0.8rem;margin:1rem 0;">
                <div style="background:rgba(255,107,43,0.08);border:1px solid rgba(255,107,43,0.2);padding:0.8rem;border-radius:8px;">
                  <strong style="color:var(--sun);">Noun</strong> — a person, place, thing or idea. <em>Dog, Zambia, happiness</em>
                </div>
                <div style="background:rgba(0,201,167,0.08);border:1px solid rgba(0,201,167,0.2);padding:0.8rem;border-radius:8px;">
                  <strong style="color:var(--teal);">Verb</strong> — an action or state. <em>Run, is, think</em>
                </div>
                <div style="background:rgba(245,166,35,0.08);border:1px solid rgba(245,166,35,0.2);padding:0.8rem;border-radius:8px;">
                  <strong style="color:var(--gold);">Adjective</strong> — describes a noun. <em>Big, red, happy</em>
                </div>
                <div style="background:rgba(255,107,43,0.08);border:1px solid rgba(255,107,43,0.2);padding:0.8rem;border-radius:8px;">
                  <strong style="color:var(--sun);">Adverb</strong> — describes a verb or adjective. <em>Quickly, very, well</em>
                </div>
              </div>
            `
          },
          {
            id: 'eng-2', title: 'Writing a Good Paragraph',
            meta: ['⏱ 25 min', '⭐ +50 pts', '📖 English'],
            content: `
              <h3 style="color:var(--sun);margin-top:0;">Structure of a Paragraph</h3>
              <p>Every good paragraph has three parts:</p>
              <div style="background:rgba(255,107,43,0.08);border-left:3px solid var(--sun);padding:1rem;border-radius:0 8px 8px 0;margin:1rem 0;">
                <p>1️⃣ <strong>Topic sentence</strong> — introduces the main idea</p>
                <p>2️⃣ <strong>Supporting sentences</strong> — give details and examples</p>
                <p>3️⃣ <strong>Concluding sentence</strong> — wraps up the idea</p>
              </div>
              <h3 style="color:var(--sun);">Example Paragraph</h3>
              <div style="background:rgba(0,201,167,0.08);border:1px solid rgba(0,201,167,0.2);padding:1rem;border-radius:8px;margin:1rem 0;font-style:italic;">
                "Water is essential for life. All living things need water to survive — humans drink it, plants absorb it through their roots, and animals find it in rivers and lakes. Without water, no organism on earth could exist."
              </div>
            `
          }
        ]
      },
      science: {
        name: 'Science', icon: '🔬', badge: 'Core',
        lessons: [
          {
            id: 'sci-1', title: 'Photosynthesis',
            meta: ['⏱ 25 min', '⭐ +50 pts', '🔬 Science'],
            content: `
              <h3 style="color:var(--sun);margin-top:0;">What is Photosynthesis?</h3>
              <p>Photosynthesis is the process by which <strong>plants make their own food</strong> using sunlight, water, and carbon dioxide.</p>
              <div style="background:rgba(255,107,43,0.08);border-left:3px solid var(--sun);padding:1rem;border-radius:0 8px 8px 0;margin:1rem 0;">
                <p>📌 The equation: <strong>CO₂ + H₂O + Sunlight → Glucose + O₂</strong></p>
              </div>
              <h3 style="color:var(--sun);">Where does it happen?</h3>
              <p>Photosynthesis happens in the <strong>chloroplasts</strong> — the green parts of plant cells. Chloroplasts contain <strong>chlorophyll</strong>, which is what makes plants green and captures sunlight.</p>
              <div style="background:rgba(0,201,167,0.08);border:1px solid rgba(0,201,167,0.2);padding:1rem;border-radius:8px;margin:1rem 0;">
                🌿 Why are plants important? They produce the oxygen we breathe and form the base of all food chains.
              </div>
            `
          }
        ]
      },
      history: {
        name: 'History', icon: '🏛️', badge: 'Popular',
        lessons: [
          {
            id: 'hist-1', title: 'The Scramble for Africa',
            meta: ['⏱ 30 min', '⭐ +50 pts', '🏛️ History'],
            content: `
              <h3 style="color:var(--sun);margin-top:0;">What was the Scramble for Africa?</h3>
              <p>The Scramble for Africa was the period between <strong>1881 and 1914</strong> when European powers rapidly colonised almost the entire African continent.</p>
              <div style="background:rgba(255,107,43,0.08);border-left:3px solid var(--sun);padding:1rem;border-radius:0 8px 8px 0;margin:1rem 0;">
                <p>📌 By 1914, only <strong>Ethiopia</strong> and <strong>Liberia</strong> remained independent African nations.</p>
              </div>
              <h3 style="color:var(--sun);">The Berlin Conference (1884–85)</h3>
              <p>European powers met in Berlin, Germany to divide Africa among themselves. African leaders were <strong>not invited</strong>. The continent was carved up based on European interests, ignoring African ethnic groups, languages, and kingdoms.</p>
              <div style="background:rgba(0,201,167,0.08);border:1px solid rgba(0,201,167,0.2);padding:1rem;border-radius:8px;margin:1rem 0;">
                🌍 Major colonial powers: Britain, France, Germany, Belgium, Portugal, Italy, Spain
              </div>
              <h3 style="color:var(--sun);">Impact on Africa</h3>
              <p>Colonisation brought forced labour, land seizure, cultural destruction, and artificial borders that still cause conflict today. However, it also introduced new infrastructure like railways and schools — though primarily built to serve European interests.</p>
            `
          },
          {
            id: 'hist-2', title: 'African Independence Movements',
            meta: ['⏱ 30 min', '⭐ +50 pts', '🏛️ History'],
            content: `
              <h3 style="color:var(--sun);margin-top:0;">The Wave of Independence</h3>
              <p>After World War II, African nations began fighting for independence. The 1950s–1970s saw most of Africa break free from colonial rule.</p>
              <div style="background:rgba(255,107,43,0.08);border-left:3px solid var(--sun);padding:1rem;border-radius:0 8px 8px 0;margin:1rem 0;">
                <p>📌 <strong>1957</strong> — Ghana becomes the first sub-Saharan African country to gain independence (from Britain)</p>
                <p>📌 <strong>1960</strong> — The "Year of Africa" — 17 countries gained independence</p>
              </div>
              <h3 style="color:var(--sun);">Key Figures</h3>
              <div style="display:grid;gap:0.8rem;margin:1rem 0;">
                <div style="background:rgba(0,201,167,0.08);border:1px solid rgba(0,201,167,0.2);padding:0.8rem;border-radius:8px;">
                  <strong style="color:var(--teal);">Kwame Nkrumah</strong> — Ghana — led peaceful independence movement, first PM and President
                </div>
                <div style="background:rgba(0,201,167,0.08);border:1px solid rgba(0,201,167,0.2);padding:0.8rem;border-radius:8px;">
