                </div>
                <div style="background:rgba(0,201,167,0.08);border:1px solid rgba(0,201,167,0.2);padding:0.8rem;border-radius:8px;">
                  <strong style="color:var(--teal);">Patrice Lumumba</strong> — Congo — first Prime Minister, advocated for pan-African unity
                </div>
              </div>
            `
          },
          {
            id: 'hist-3', title: 'World War I — Causes and Effects',
            meta: ['⏱ 35 min', '⭐ +50 pts', '🏛️ History'],
            content: `
              <h3 style="color:var(--sun);margin-top:0;">The MAIN Causes</h3>
              <p>Historians use the acronym <strong>MAIN</strong> to summarise the causes of World War I:</p>
              <div style="display:grid;gap:0.8rem;margin:1rem 0;">
                <div style="background:rgba(255,107,43,0.08);border:1px solid rgba(255,107,43,0.2);padding:0.8rem;border-radius:8px;">
                  <strong style="color:var(--sun);">M</strong> — Militarism: European nations built up massive armies and navies
                </div>
                <div style="background:rgba(255,107,43,0.08);border:1px solid rgba(255,107,43,0.2);padding:0.8rem;border-radius:8px;">
                  <strong style="color:var(--sun);">A</strong> — Alliances: Secret agreements meant one conflict dragged in many nations
                </div>
                <div style="background:rgba(255,107,43,0.08);border:1px solid rgba(255,107,43,0.2);padding:0.8rem;border-radius:8px;">
                  <strong style="color:var(--sun);">I</strong> — Imperialism: Competition for African and Asian colonies created tensions
                </div>
                <div style="background:rgba(255,107,43,0.08);border:1px solid rgba(255,107,43,0.2);padding:0.8rem;border-radius:8px;">
                  <strong style="color:var(--sun);">N</strong> — Nationalism: Strong national pride, especially in the Balkans
                </div>
              </div>
              <h3 style="color:var(--sun);">The Trigger</h3>
              <div style="background:rgba(0,201,167,0.08);border:1px solid rgba(0,201,167,0.2);padding:1rem;border-radius:8px;margin:1rem 0;">
                💥 On 28 June 1914, Archduke Franz Ferdinand of Austria-Hungary was assassinated in Sarajevo. This triggered the alliance system and started the war.
              </div>
            `
          }
        ]
      },
      geography: {
        name: 'Geography', icon: '🌍', badge: 'Popular',
        lessons: [
          {
