                🏜️ <strong>Desert</strong> — Very hot and dry. Sahara (North Africa), Kalahari (South Africa).<br><br>
                🌿 <strong>Mediterranean</strong> — Hot dry summers, mild wet winters. Cape Town, North Africa coast.
              </div>
            `
          },
          {
            id: 'geo-2', title: 'Rivers and Water Systems',
            meta: ['⏱ 25 min', '⭐ +50 pts', '🌍 Geography'],
            content: `
              <h3 style="color:var(--sun);margin-top:0;">Major African Rivers</h3>
              <p>Rivers are vital for transport, farming, electricity, and drinking water across Africa.</p>
              <div style="display:grid;gap:0.8rem;margin:1rem 0;">
                <div style="background:rgba(0,201,167,0.08);border:1px solid rgba(0,201,167,0.2);padding:0.8rem;border-radius:8px;">
                  <strong style="color:var(--teal);">The Nile</strong> — 6,650 km — World's longest river. Flows through Uganda, Sudan, Egypt.
